  "text": "In 119 patients with recurrent infections following a Girdlestone procedure, Suda et al. [CITATION_1] demonstrated 100% infection control using a vastus lateralis interposition flap implanted into the acetabular cavity using Mitek anchors. The acetabular cavity was deemed the source of recurrent infection after the Girdlestone procedure.",
